code_data:
import boto3

s3 = boto3.resource('s3')
for bucket in s3.buckets.all():
    print(bucket.name)
explanation: The code uses the boto3 library to create a resource object for S3 and iterates over all buckets, printing their names. It assumes that AWS credentials are correctly configured in the environment.
